OriginalAxioms:
:Weariness rdfs:comment Weariness is an internal Sensation which causes
           an urge to relax, either physically or mentally.  This 
           Feeling has several levels of intensity.
          
          Corresponds to noun sense 1 of weariness,sense 1 of tiredness and
          sense 1 of fatigue in WordNet; fatigue is usually interpreted as more intense
          than just weariness but these words are not sufficiently distinct in meaning
          to differentiate them logically.
            1. 2 fatigue, weariness, tiredness - temporary loss of strength 
               and energy resulting from hard physical or mental work;
               he was hospitalized for extreme fatigue; growing fatigue was
               apparent from the decline in the execution of their athletic skills;
               weariness overcame her after twelve hours and she fell asleep

:Fastener rdfs:comment A PhysicalObject whose purpose is to attach one thing 
          to something else, e.g. nails, screws, buttons, etc.
          For cases where a quantity of cement or glue, or a piece of tape
          is used for Fastening, use the parent type FasteningObject.
          This type is reserved for SolidObjects.  NOTE that a piece of lacing such as a shoelace 
          or one loop of  a thread that is sewn into objects to hold them together is also
          a Fastener
          
          In SUMO called AttachingDevice.
          
          Tools that apply Fasteners hammer, stapler are
          FasteningTools.
          
          In Cyc called Connector
          Cyc: A specialization of #$NonPoweredDevice.  Each
            instance of #$Connector is a device which connects two
            objects.  An instance of #$Connector may be a part
            incorporated into one or both of the objects connected, or
            it may be a totally separate device.  Notable
            specializations of #$Connector include #$Staple, #$Pin, and #$Nail.
            
            Corresponds to noun sense 2 of fastener in WordNet:
              2. fastener, fastening, holdfast, fixing - restraint that attaches
                 to something or holds something in place

:Civilian rdfs:comment Persons who are not members of military organizations.
        
        SUMO: Someone who is not a member of a ModernMilitaryOrganization.
        
          Corresponds to noun sense 1 of civilian in Wordnet:
             1. 2 civilian - a nonmilitary citizen

:Spoke rdfs:comment A Spoke is a  Rod made of some rigid material, that connects the
           Hub and WheelRim of a Wheel. 
           
            Corresponds to noun sense 1 of spoke in Wordnet:
               1. 2 spoke, wheel spoke, radius - support consisting of a radial member 
                 of a wheel joining the hub to the rim

:Word rdfs:comment A term of some Language that plays the Role of Designator for
       some concept.  It is an AbstractString, even if it consists of a single
       ideogram or hieroglyph.  therefore this does not include the sounds that
       are spoken words.  It is an AbstractString that, in any given usage,
       is intended to symbolize a single concept - though in different contexts the
       same Word may have different meanings, and in puns the meaning may be intended
       to be ambiguous or fluctuating. It is also an AbstractSymbol.  There is 
       some debate over what should linguistically constitute a Word.
       In the English language, a string of characters that is not broken by spaces 
       can be considered as a Word, even if it is nonsensical.  Tightly linked groups of character 
       strings that have meaning that cannot be constructed from the individual
       character strings e.g. idioms that are not sentences can also be
       considered here as Words; if the meaning of a Word with spaces in it
       is deducible from its components, it should be classified as a Phrase.
       
       Corresponds to part the sbatract string part of noun sense 1 of word in WordNet:
         1. 958 word - a unit of language that native speakers can identify; 
           words are the blocks from which sentences are made; he hardly said ten
           words all morning

:Saturn rdfs:comment 
         Corresponds to noun sense 1 of Saturn in Wordnet:
            1. 3 Saturn - a giant planet that is surrounded by three planar concentric rings 
              of ice particles; the 6th planet from the sun

:Tar rdfs:comment A PhysicalSubstance consisting mostly of high-boiling linear or
     branch-chained Hydrocarbons,found naturally or obtained as the residue
     of petroleumrefining process.
     
        Corresponds to noun sense 1 of tar in WordNet:
          1. 1 pitch, tar - any of various dark heavy viscid substances obtained as a residue

:CleaningEvent rdfs:comment COSMO note: in COSMO this is interpreted as including
          an Event in which an undesirable substance is removed from
          a substance of which it is part, even when the contaminant
          is not in solid form.  Thus deionizing water would be a CleaningEvent.
          
          Cyc: A collection of events and a specialization of
            #$RemovingSomething and #$TakingCareOfSomething.  In each
            #$Cleaning event, dirt or some other unwanted substance is
            removed from the #$objectOfStateChange of that event.  If a
            #$Cleaning event is successful, then the #$Dirtiness level
            of the object will have been lowered. A notable
            specialization of this collection is #$Scrubbing.
            
              Corresponds to verb sense 1 of clean in Wordnet:
                 1. 16 clean, make clean - make clean by removing dirt, filth, 
                 or unwanted substances from; Clean the stove!; The dentist cleaned my teeth

:Blower rdfs:comment A PropellingDevice that causes a current of a Gas
           to flow, whether into free air or through some tube or orifice.
           
           Corresponds to noun sense 1 of blower in Wordnet:
              1. 3 blower - a device that produces a current of air

:Dead rdfs:comment An attribute that specifies that an animal is dead no longer living, - 
    meaningful only when asserted at a particular time.
    Disjoint with alive.
    ***Note that a person can be Dead and still be a Person.  This may differ
    from some usages.  The fact that a Person is Dead is reflected in the
    VitalityAtribute, not in its existence***
    NOTE that an animal that is dead in this sense can never again be alive.  For the 
    situation where an animal has no vital signs, but then revives, see the
    attribute ClinicallyDead.
    
    Corresponds to part of adjective sense 1 of dead in WordNet,
      however, this applies only to organisms or cellular structures, and the sense suggested
      by dead pallor is not included in this type.
      1. 72 dead - no longer having or seeming to have or expecting to have life;
    the nerve is dead; a dead pallor; he was marked as a dead man by the assassin

:Shameful rdfs:comment Shameful is an AttributeValue of actions
          which are of a type that are considered as being obviously
          improper by the community in which they are performed.
          WordNet has two senses that seem to diifer only slightly in the
          degree of shamefulness, the higher degree sense 2 being
          scandalous or shocking.  There may be a distinction based on the 
          inherent character of an action and its likelihood of leading to
          opprobrium, but that is not yet distinguished in COSMO.  This
          AttributeValue includes all senses.
          
          WordNet:
           1. 2 black, disgraceful, ignominious, inglorious, opprobrious, shameful
               - used of conduct or character deserving or bringing disgrace or shame;
               Man...has written one of his blackest records as a destroyer on 
                the oceanic islands - Rachel Carson; an ignominious retreat; 
                inglorious defeat; an opprobrious monument to human greed;
                a shameful display of cowardice
           2. disgraceful, scandalous, shameful, shocking - giving offense to moral
               sensibilities and injurious to reputation; scandalous behavior;
               the wicked rascally shameful conduct of the bankrupt  - Thackeray;
               the most shocking book of its time

:hasMassInGrams rdfs:comment hasMassInGrams relates an Object to its mass measured
       in grams.  This is a shortcut to using more general functional
       mass measures, and is used here only for illustration,
       to permit some specifics in instances.  The values given should
       be taken as crude estimates order of magnitude estimates,
       possible error over 100%, particularly since no time
       interval is given by this relation.  Relations expressing
       more exact values of mass have not yet v0.45 been written
       in COSMO.  This is mostly a placeholder for more
       meaningful relations.
       
       NOTE that for convenience we allow FictionalThings to have a 
         mass, though they are not PhysicalObjects.
      
       NOTE: for objects whose mass is unknown, a value of -1 will
        serve as the code for unknown mass.  Since, as of v0.49, a 
        mass value is required in COSMO for PhysicalObjects mass is
        the characteristic property of PhysicalObjects, an explicit
        value must be provided even if it is unknown.
        If an approximate value can be guessed within +- 100% as with
        human weights,a value should be entered so that the reasoner will 
        have some information with which to make inferences.  For example, a car 
        mass of 1,000,000 grams one ton will allow the reasoner to 
        infer too heavy for a person to lift.
        
        NOTE: for the restriction, MentalObject was added as an additional
        domain to allow descriptions of Fictional objects to have
        mass attributed.  @ToDo: refactor in a more meaningful way?
        
        The use of this relation implies some prior measurement or estimate
          of mass, suggeting some relation to verb sense 1 of weigh in WordNet:
         1. 19 weigh - have a certain weight
:Certificate-IBT rdfs:comment This is the original Cyc 0.78 name for Certificate.

:ClothingItem rdfs:comment A single connected article of clothing,
            such as one shoe, one shirt, or a pair
            of pants.
            
          Cyc: A specialization of #$Clothing-Generic.  Each
            instance of #$ClothingItem is something that a person wears
            as a protective and/or decorative covering or ornament.
            Items of clothing are usually made of flexible materials,
            such as cloth, leather, or yarn.  The collection
            #$ClothingItem contains primarily individual garments e.g.,
            instances of the collections #$Pants, #$Shirt, #$Coat,
            #$Shoe, together with pairs of shoes, socks, and gloves
            since each wearer needs a pair.  Jewelry, suspenders,
            belts, etc., are in the specialization #$ClothingAccessory.
            Note: outfits esp. specialized outfits made up of several
            individual items worn together belong to the collection
            #$ClothingOutfit, which is _not_ a specialization of
            #$ClothingItem but _is_ a specialization of the broader
            collection, #$SomethingToWear.
            
            Corresponds to sense 1 of clothing in WordNet:
            1. 9 clothing, article of clothing, vesture, wear, wearable, habiliment -
              a covering designed to be worn on a persons body
            See Clothes for difference between clothes and clothing
            in WordNet.

:HurricaneAsObject rdfs:comment A cyclone with high-speed winds and thunderstorms.
            See also #$HurricaneAsEvent.
          
          Wordnet makes no distinction betweenhe Event and Object aspects of a hurricane:
           Corresponds to noun sense 1 of hurricane in Wordnet:
              1. 2 hurricane - a severe tropical cyclone usually with heavy rains and winds 
              moving a 73-136 knots 12 on the Beaufort scale

:Polysaccharide rdfs:comment A Carbohyhdrate having more than 5 linked
           monosaccharide rings in each molecule.

:HumanHair rdfs:comment The Substance Hair that is growing on some part of
          a Person.
        
           CYC HumanHair-Stuff: The collection of the material of which
            #$Hair-Strands of instances of #$HomoSapiens are composed.

:Party-Celebration rdfs:comment A specialization of #$SocialGathering.  Each
            instance of #$Party-Celebration is a social gathering whose
            main purpose is the entertainment, amusement, or pleasure of
            those gathered.  Specializations of #$Party-Celebration
            include #$BirthdayParty, #$DinnerParty, and #$BabyShower.
            
            This is characterized as Pleasant - which is the purpose,
              though not always the result.
            
            Corresponds to noun sense 2 of party in WordNet:
            2. 126 party - an occasion on which people can assemble for social 
               interaction and entertainment; he planned a party to celebrate Bastille Day

:ProductObject rdfs:comment ProductObject is an Artifact produced for sale:
      This differes from parent Product in that it is a PhysicalObject,
      and cannot be a substance or service which is not usually referred to as a product
      except informally or metaphorically.

      Although SUMO requires a ProductObject to be manufactured,
        an agricultural product or raw material extracted from the Earth
        is also included in this COSMO type,
        such as an ear of corn conforming with the WordNet usage of product.
        Any Object sold at retail or wholesale is a ProductObject.
        @ToDo: It is possible to distinguish things offered for sale wares,
          merchandise as a subtype of things
          produced for sale, but that is left to a later elaboration.
    
       SUMO: An Artifact that is produced by Manufacture and that is 
         intended to be sold.
     
       Corresponds to noun sense 2 of product, sense 4 of good usually used in the
         plural, as goods, sense 2 of ware and
         sense 1 of merchandise in WordNet :
      WN good
        4. commodity, trade good, good - articles of commerce.
      WN product
        2. 138 product, production - an artifact that has been created by someone 
           or some process; they improve their product every year; 
          they export most of their agricultural production
      WN ware:
        2. merchandise, ware, product - - commodities offered for sale;
        good business depends on having good merchandise; that store offers a
        variety of products
      WN noun thing:
        3. 224 thing - an artifact; how does this thing work?

:Licorice rdfs:comment 
          Corresponds to noun sense 2 of licorice in WordNet:
            2. licorice, liquorice - a black candy flavored with the dried root of the licorice plant

:EuroDollar rdfs:comment A currency measure used in most European Union countries.
    
       Corresponds to noun sense 1 of eurodollar in Wordnet:
          1. Eurodollar - a United States dollar deposited in a European bank and used as an 
            international currency to finance trade

:Internet rdfs:comment An Internet is a specific type of computer Network using
            specific protocols, though the physical parts of it may change from day to day.
            This includes the network referred to as The Internet.  According to the 
            restriction, there may be more than one Internet but to fit into
            this category that network has to include one set of servers InternetServers01
            that includes the computer InternetServer001
            
            
            Should This be an instance?
            
           Corresponds to noun sense 1 of internet in Wordnet:
              1. internet, net, cyberspace - a computer network consisting of a worldwide
                 network of computer networks that use the TCP/IP network protocols to 
                 facilitate data transmission and exchange

:Rooster rdfs:comment The adult female of the domestic Chicken.
        
         Corresponds to noun sense 1 of rooster in Wordnet:
            1. 3 cock, rooster - adult male chicken

:DrummingSound rdfs:comment A DrummingSound is a Sound consisting of more than two
          low-pitched short sounds characteristic  of a drum being beaten.

          A sound Similar to RHW rub-a-dub
             the sound of a drum when beaten.
            
          This is similar to the intransitive  component of the verbdrum in WN,
            and similar to rub-a-dub in RHW::            
          1. 1 drum, beat, thrum - make a rhythmic sound; 
            Rain drummed against the windshield; The drums beat all night

:hasMonomerUnit rdfs:comment hasMonomerUnit relates a Polymer a Substance to the type of chemical unit
       an Object that is repeated in the chain..

:Precise rdfs:comment Able to measure with a high degree of accuracy -
          of measuring instruments.
          
          For the quality of actions that exactly or almost exactly
          achieve their desired effect,use Preciseness.
          For assertions that conform to the reality of the world
          they are intended to represent, use Exact.

:Gecko rdfs:comment A group of lizard species that are best known for
             their sticky foot pads which allow them to cling to smooth
             surfaces. Most species are tropical, nocturnal insectivores.

:Reservation rdfs:comment Any kind of reservation, where one agent agrees to reserve
    something for another agent - airline seats, hotel rooms, merchandise.
    
    The is not the action of reserving something, it is a type of Agreement, a mentalObject.
    
      Corresponds to part of noun sense 5 of reservation in Wordnet:
         5. reservation - the written record or promise of an arrangement by which 
         accommodations are secured in advance

:tableCorrespondsToEntities rdfs:comment tableCorrespondsToEntities points from
         A MultipleEntityTable to multiple Entities each specified
         in a separate relation in the ontology
         that the DatabaseTable is intended to represent.
         When more than one entity in an ontology is represented by a 
         Table, there should be at least one field column which
         contains an indicator as to which Type in the ontology is
         being represented in a particular row record.

:ElectricalWire rdfs:comment In COSMO ElectricalWire is any conductive wire an Object used to
           transmit electrical current, for use as a power surce or for
           transmiission of signals,as in telephone and telegraph equipment.
        
           CYC. Wire used as an electrical conductor, usually
            housed in insulation of some sort.
            
              Corresponds to noun sense 1 of conducting wire in WordNet:
                1. 2 wire, conducting wire - a metal conductor that carries 
                      electricity over a distance

:Darkness rdfs:comment Darkness is an EnvironmentalSituation in which there is a very low
          level or complete absence of VisibleLight.
          
          Corresponds to noun sense 1 of darkness in Wordnet:
             1. 20 dark, darkness - absence of light or illumination

:RemainingPart rdfs:comment A RemainingPart of an Object is a ProperPart of
           that Object that is still Extant at some particular time.

:Funny rdfs:comment Funny is Amusing in a way that causes at least some
            people to laugh.  There may be disagreement as to whether a 
            specific thing is Funny, therefore this is a subtype of EvaluativeAttribute.
            Something more generally considered as funny is labeled as Humorous.

          This may be used for attempts at humor evoking  Thats not funny.
          
          For Events that are Funny,see FunnyEvent.
          
          Corresponds to adjective sense 1 of funny and sense 2 of amusing and 
            sense 1 of comical in WordNet:
            1. amusing, comic, comical, funny, laughable, mirthful, risible -
                arousing or provoking laughter; an amusing film with a steady
                stream of pranks and pratfalls; an amusing fellow; a comic hat;
                a comical look of surprise; funny stories that made everybody laugh;
                a very funny writer; it would have been laughable if it hadnt hurt so much;
                a mirthful experience; risible courtroom antics
             .

:LinguisticDesignator rdfs:comment A LinguisticDesignator is a Symbol used in some HumanLanguage,
       whether natural or artificial.  This type includes spoken as well as written words
       or Terms.

:SecuritiesExchange rdfs:comment Each instance of SecuritiesExchange is some Organization that 
          has instituted procedures and methods for buying and selling of
          FinancialSecuritys - stocks, bonds, commodities futures, puts and calls, etc.
        
          Includes but is not limited to noun sense 1 of securities market in
             WordNet:
            1. stock exchange, stock market, securities market - an exchange where
              security trading is conducted by professional stockbrokers
        .

:hasTypicalHabitat rdfs:comment hasTypicalHabitat relates some OrganismType
           to some type of region or environment in which the
           naturally free-living organisms of that Type are usually found.

:LongAndThinObject rdfs:comment An Object, physical or abstract, that is
          LongAndThin.  A LongAndThinObject doesnt have to be very
          long,just 5 times longer than the diameter or width.
          
          A LongAndThinObject has exactly two ends.
          .

:Education rdfs:comment The Knowledge one gains by being educated.  A Group of many bits 
    of Knowledge as well as some
    general skills at being able to acquire more knowledge, usually 
    acquired by a formal process of Educating, though self-education
    is possible.
    
    NOTE that Knowledge and Education are considered as composed of 
    multiple individual facts, or pieces of knowledge, so the content of
    a full education can be considered Knowledge as well as each of the
    component facts.
    
     Corresponds to noun sense 2 of education in WordNet:
        2. 10 education - knowledge acquired by learning and instruction;
         it was clear that he had a very broad education

:LawSuit rdfs:comment A Lawsuit is a LegalAction in which one Agent
         enters a suit in a governmental court against another LegalAgent,
         to obtain some remedy for a grievance.  Each instance
         of Lawsuit includes and all subsequent actions in the same case,
        up to final disposition.
        
        CYC: The collection of legal conflicts in which an
            agent or group of agents pursues a court case against
            another agent or group of agents.  A law suit may be
            settled, dropped, dismissed, or go to trial.
            
            Corresponds to noun sense 1 of suit in WordNet:
             1. 390 lawsuit, suit, case, cause, causa -
               a comprehensive term for any proceeding in a court of law
               whereby an individual seeks a legal remedy; 
               the family brought suit against the landlord

:LivingProcess rdfs:comment Living is the process not Event of being alive,
      specific for organisms.  To be Living does not necessarily
      mean that an Organism is actively metabolizing; like a seed
      or spore, it may be dormant.  However, viruses, which cannot
      metabolize outside of the cell of another organism, are
      not able to be Living. In COSMO a synonym for 
      Living is BiologicalSurvival.
      
      For surviving meaning to persist through some potentially threatening
       Event use SurvivingAnEvent.

ceed4a8d-5892-40a7-893c-882fe879c0d7 rdfs:subClassOf A term of some Language that plays the Role of Designator for
       some concept.  It is an AbstractString, even if it consists of a single
       ideogram or hieroglyph.  therefore this does not include the sounds that
       are spoken words.  It is an AbstractString that, in any given usage,
       is intended to symbolize a single concept - though in different contexts the
       same Word may have different meanings, and in puns the meaning may be intended
       to be ambiguous or fluctuating. It is also an AbstractSymbol.  There is 
       some debate over what should linguistically constitute a Word.
       In the English language, a string of characters that is not broken by spaces 
       can be considered as a Word, even if it is nonsensical.  Tightly linked groups of character 
       strings that have meaning that cannot be constructed from the individual
       character strings e.g. idioms that are not sentences can also be
       considered here as Words; if the meaning of a Word with spaces in it
       is deducible from its components, it should be classified as a Phrase.
       
       Corresponds to part the sbatract string part of noun sense 1 of word in WordNet:
         1. 958 word - a unit of language that native speakers can identify; 
           words are the blocks from which sentences are made; he hardly said ten
           words all morning
